Center: IAEA Nuclear Data Section, Vienna, Austria
title: A study of protons from In-115 and Au-197 with 14.8 MeV incident neutrons

x4freetext: Full information
A study of protons from In-115 and Au-197 with 14.8 MeV
incident neutrons
D(t,n)He4.
Triple coincidence method
Telescope consisted of two propor-
tional counters in coincidence with a CsI(Tl) scintil-
lation counter plus a proportional counter in antico-
incidence.
Neutron intensity monitored with Hornyak button
Energy calibration from recoil proton spectrum
from elastic scattering of neutrons in polyethylene.
Protons
Proton spectra corrected for absorption losses due to
target thickness.
Metal In-115 target was 32.8 mg/cm2 thick and
3cm in diameter.
Target was 12cm from neutron source.
Data given is from private communication and is incon-
sistent with Nucl.Phys.47,473(1963),Fig.3 and data
derived by compiler from fig.1. However data from all
sources fall within error bars of fig.3
Data received from H.S.Hans,March 1967
data may be derived from entries
30055.007-010 within limits noted in last comment above
Compiled into Dastar-00228
Transformed from Dastar to EXFOR
No correction in addition to use of an electronic
blocking circuit was made for possible contamination
of spectrum by (n,d) deuterons below 8 MeV.
Estimated angular spread is +- 17 degrees
errors vary from 10-20% in the measured values
from forward to back angles.
